 digital era, especially in online social media and virtual environments where so many children now spend a great deal of time, and explores the implications for children and for regulators.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBrand name products. 0aBranding (Marketing). 0aChild consumers. 0aInternet advertising and children. 0aMass media and children. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Marketing / General.2bisacsh  aAdvertising.  aBranding.  aChildren.  aConsumers.  aDigital Branding.  aMarketing.1 aGunter, Barrie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499710640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784997106423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784997106/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles